  "instructions": [
    "In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.",
    "Add lardons and cook until golden brown, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add onion and garlic; sauté for another 3-4 minutes or until onions are translucent.",
    "Stir in lentils, water, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer covered for 20 minutes.",
    "Gently fold in parsley if using.",
    "Once cooked through and tender (about 50 minutes total), adjust seasoning as needed.",
